#compdef spacedrive
# =============================================================================
# spacedrive — Spacedrive v2 CLI (daemon client).  Spacedrive is an
#              open-source cross-platform file explorer powered by a Rust
#              core and a decentralized peer-to-peer database (Spacetime
#              DB), designed as an "iCloud / Google Drive / Dropbox
#              replacement that you control".  The `spacedrive` binary is
#              the official CLI client for the spacedrive daemon: it
#              starts/stops/restarts the daemon, queries indexed file
#              locations, manages libraries and tags, monitors the event
#              bus in real-time, drives sync between paired devices,
#              orchestrates jobs (thumbnail-gen, indexing, etc.), and —
#              critically — drives the INTERACTIVE CLOUD-STORAGE PAIRING
#              flow via `spacedrive cloud` which walks the user through
#              an inquire-driven prompt sequence to enroll a Spacedrive
#              cloud instance.
#
